12... Ba6 { Attacking the pawn on d3 and forcing the issue. } 13. g4 Nh6
{ The knight is forced back to the edge but it has come at a price for White: playing g4 has weakened White's king. }
14. d4
{ The best way of dealing with the threat to the d-pawn. Instead,  14.c4  f5  15.exf6  exf6  is a tricky position for White having weakened the kingside. }
