{ The knight returns from the edge and puts pressure on the e5-pawn.   By the way,  11...Nxg4?  has been tried in a few games but this boldness rebounds badly. White gets a powerful attack after  12.hxg4  fxe5  13.Rxh7  Kxh7  14.Ng5+  Kg8  15.Be3  followed by queenside castling. }
12. e6
{ Black should not fear this move as the knight moves into the centre and the e6-pawn is often vulnerable. }
12... Nd6 13. O-O-O Nb5
{ White has an awkward decision to make with the knight on c3. Best is to exchange on b5, but that opens lines for Black's counter-attack on the queenside. }
14. Nxb5 cxb5 15. Rhe1 b4
{ followed by ...Qd5 and Black's counter-attack begins. } *

