8. O-O
{ The king should exit before anything else is undertaken. Traditionally, the normal move here is  8...Nge7  - with a probable transposition to a French Tarrasch after  9.Nbd2  . This is a reasonable way for Black to play. However, it has recently been discovered that Black can play more actively with  8...Nf6  . It was always thought that White could exploit the open e-file, but practice has shown that Black is not troubled and more than that, can often seize the initiative. }
