11. Bxc6
{ This isn't quite as bad as taking with the knight, but White must play accurately to avoid disadvantage. }
11... bxc6 12. Bg5 Bd7
{ Now that White is developing, Black should act prudently and protect the threatened pawns. }
13. Nd2 h6
{ It cannot hurt to throw in this useful pawn move. Of course, exchanging bishop for knight would only benefit Black. }
14. Bh4 Be7
{ I think this retreat is the most prudent from Black's viewpoint. The other way to break the pin was  14...g5  , but in this case I would prefer not to weaken the king - Black has to play accurately to equalise. }
15. Qf3 Re8
{ The strong pawn on d5 means that it is hard for White to achieve anything here. }
16. h3 a5
{ The pawn would like to step forward again so that the b2-pawn becomes a target. Chances are balanced. }
