{ Attacking f2. } 13. Rf1 Ne4 { And again. } 14. Qe1 Rfe8
{ White's pieces are so badly placed, it isn't possible to escape Black's pressure. }
15. b4 Bd6 16. Be3 Qc7
{ Black has been driven away from the attack on f2, but switches diagonals to attack h2. If  17.h3  , Black replies  17...Qd7  with a deadly and unstoppable sacrifice on h3 coming soon. }
17. f4
{ Incredibly ugly, but forced. Black's knight cannot be shifted from e4 and White is positionally bust. }
17... Bf5 18. Bd3 a5 19. bxa5 Qxa5
{ Black's control over the e4-square, pressure on the e-file, strong centre pawns and pressure on the weak c3 and a2-pawns, all add up to a winning position. }
