{ White has arrived at a fairly typical GPA pawn sacrifice position, but with a couple of crucial differences: Black's knight is actively placed on d4, and that knight on h6 is also about to play an active role in the game. }
10... Ng4 11. Nxd4 Bxd4+ 12. Kh1 Nxh2
{ Gives Black a winning attack. The knight on h6 can play a great role in these variations. }
