10... Ng4 11. Kh1 { White needs to take care. } 11... Kh8
{ The king steps away from potential trouble on the diagonal. There is no rush, Black can hold the tension. }
12. h3 fxe4 13. dxe4 Nxf3
{ With this exchange Black secures control over the e5-square as  14.gxf3  Qh4  gives Black a crushing attack. }
14. Qxf3 Ne5 15. Qe2 d6
{ With the dominant knight on e5, not to mention the extra pawn, Black has a clear advantage. }
