Nf3 { 4.Bc4  is the alternative, considered in the previous chapter. } 4... e6
{ Preparing to develop the kingside. This appeals to me as it leaves the bishop dangling ineffectively on b5.   Nevertheless, Black can also play  4...Nxb5  5.Nxb5  d6  6.d4  Nf6  7.Nc3  cxd4  8.Qxd4  e5  10.Qd3  h6  which is closely related to the Najdorf and 3.Bb5+ Nd7 lines. Which fourth move you choose is a question of taste. }
