{ Already, strong computers aren't particularly impressed by White's position - around minus 0.20 for those that take an interest in the digits. From a human viewpoint we can at least say that White will do well to equalise from the opening @@StartBracket@@with the proviso that Black plays well@@EndBracket@@. }
9. Be3
{ This is by far the most popular move at this juncture. The bishop covers the d4-square. Black has several good replies. The old move was  9...Nd4  , which is fine, although Black needs to be aware of  10.e5  , with which Spassky, and a few others, had some success. But I prefer 9...b6. }
