{ The knight hits the d4-outpost, supported by pawn, knight and bishop. } 13.
Ne5 exd5 14. Nxd5 Bb7
{ Attacking the knight in the middle.  14...Be6  is also playable. } 15. c4
{ Supporting the knight is best. Instead,  15.Nf6+  Qxf6  16.Bxb7  Rad8  is more pleasant to play for Black than White. }
15... Qd6
{ The recommended computer move, putting pressure on the e5-knight. The position is complex, but the strongly placed knight on d4 and the well-placed bishops on g7 and b7 give Black grounds for optimism. }
