{ Looking at moving to g4, poking the bishop. } 11. f3 O-O
{ It's about time the king evacuated. } 12. c4
{ Giving up on playing d4 is a compromise, but the break simply isn't feasible: if  12.d4  d5!  and Black's pieces are better prepared for when the position opens. }
12... b5
{ Black takes the initiative with a positional pawn sacrifice. If  13.b3  b4  , followed by advancing the a-pawn. }
13. cxb5 Nd4 14. Nbc3 Rab8
{ It is possible to recapture the pawn straightaway, but this is stronger. }
15. b3 Ne8 { Followed by ...Nc7 and recapturing on b5 with the knight. } *

