4. d3
{ A solid move, but not one to cause sleepless nights. This is very similar to Closed Sicilian positions @@StartBracket@@although White has been unable to play g3@@EndBracket@@. If Black plays  4...e5  , the position already looks equal to me. For example:  4...e5  5.Nd5  Ne7  6.Nec3  d6  7.Nxe7  Bxe7  8.Nd5  O-O  , etc. But we could be a little more adventurous and fianchetto the king's bishop. }
